<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="64" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,738]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,337,487,513]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from a Latin word ‘ 
<emphasis box="[922,1009,488,513]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">unicus’</emphasis>
meaning ‘only’, ‘singular’ or ‘sole’ for emphasizing peculiar morphologies of the puparium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,152,738]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,319,562,588]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Remarks.</emphasis>
The puparia of this species are distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName box="[1029,1165,562,587]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Asiothrixus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1165,562,587]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Asiothrixus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the narrow elongate shape and by the presence of long cephalic setae, reaching beyond the puparial margin, capitate submarginal setae and scallop-shaped markings on submedian area. It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1258,637,663]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurothrixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smilaceti">
<emphasis box="[1120,1138,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1152,1258,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">smilaceti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of siphons on abdominal segments II and III (in 
<taxonomicName box="[697,838,674,700]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurothrixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smilaceti">
<emphasis box="[697,715,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[731,838,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">smilaceti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the basal parts of siphons are much enlarged and rounded), capitate submarginal setae, long cephalic setae and scallop-shaped markings on submedian area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
